channel.title: Portfowarding Problem?
channel.description:
So I bought a router today (netgear) with optus.
Now, the problem is my ISP settings.... these are them..
IP address: 10.1.1.2 Subnet mask: 225.225.225.0 default Gateway: 10.1.1.1
Those are not normal...
I portfowarded using the IP you see above ^. Yes, it will work when I run my server on my host, but only until the no-ip thing updates.... when it updates it just changing it to my ip at ipchicken.com
But that won't work when I run the server, any ideas?
